    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Removal - Rocker Arm Carrier</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.2.5" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Rocker Arm Carrier</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not remove just one cylinder head bolt. All bolts and the head gasket
                    must be replaced. The removal and installation of one cylinder head bolt to access a rocker arm will
                    compromise the cylinder head gasket seal which will cause serious engine damage.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e300522" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08096.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rocker arm carrier assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm carrier mounting bolts (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Cylinder head bolts (8)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rocker arm carrier assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hole provided for mounting stud</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two rocker arm carrier bolts (M8 x 50) and eight cylinder head bolts (M14 x 194)
                using a circular pattern to loosen. Begin with the outer bolts and loosen bolts moving inward.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300523" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the rocker arm carrier</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift rocker arm carrier assembly from cylinder head and set aside for disassembly, cleaning,
                inspection, and assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
